From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: LibreScoot <info@librescoot.org>
Date: Sat, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: detect cable via PHY resistive plugged-in detection

The MDB is a self-powered USB gadget with no VBUS from the host.
The default g_dnl_board_usb_cable_connected() returns -EOPNOTSUPP,
so the UMS command can never detect cable disconnect and runs forever.

Use the i.MX6UL USB PHY's non-standard resistive plugged-in detection
(ENDEVPLUGINDET) which connects 200kohm pull-ups to D+/D- and reads
DEVPLUGIN_STATUS to determine if a host is connected. This works
purely through the data lines, independent of VBUS.

With this patch, `ums 0 mmc 1; reset` exits when the USB cable is
unplugged, and the chained reset reboots the board.

Tested on unu MDB (i.MX6UL) with USBPHY1 at 0x020C9000.

---
 board/freescale/mx6ul_14x14_evk/mx6ul_14x14_evk.c | 27 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)

diff --git a/board/freescale/mx6ul_14x14_evk/mx6ul_14x14_evk.c b/board/freescale/mx6ul_14x14_evk/mx6ul_14x14_evk.c
index e3ad006cf07..PLACEHOLDER 100644
--- a/board/freescale/mx6ul_14x14_evk/mx6ul_14x14_evk.c
+++ b/board/freescale/mx6ul_14x14_evk/mx6ul_14x14_evk.c
@@ -13,6 +13,7 @@
 #include <asm/imx-common/iomux-v3.h>
 #include <asm/imx-common/boot_mode.h>
 #include <asm/imx-common/mxc_i2c.h>
+#include <asm/io.h>
 #include <mmc.h>
 #include <fsl_esdhc.h>
 #include <miiphy.h>
@@ -424,6 +425,32 @@ int board_mmc_init(bd_t *bis)
 #define USB_OTHERREGS_OFFSET	0x800
 #define UCTRL_PWR_POL		(1 << 9)

+/*
+ * USB cable detection via PHY resistive plugged-in detection.
+ *
+ * The MDB has no VBUS from the host (self-powered gadget), so we use the
+ * USB PHY's built-in 200kohm pull-up resistors on D+/D- to detect whether
+ * a host cable is connected. When connected, the host's 15kohm pull-downs
+ * create a voltage divider that the PHY can measure.
+ *
+ * USBPHY1 (OTG1 gadget port):
+ *   CTRL register (base+0x30): bit 4 = ENDEVPLUGINDET (enable detection)
+ *   STATUS register (base+0x40): bit 6 = DEVPLUGIN_STATUS (1=connected)
+ */
+#define USBPHY1_BASE		0x020C9000
+#define USBPHY1_CTRL_SET	(USBPHY1_BASE + 0x34)
+#define USBPHY1_STATUS		(USBPHY1_BASE + 0x40)
+#define CTRL_ENDEVPLUGINDET	(1 << 4)
+#define STATUS_DEVPLUGIN	(1 << 6)
+
+int g_dnl_board_usb_cable_connected(void)
+{
+	/* Enable resistive detection if not already on */
+	writel(CTRL_ENDEVPLUGINDET, USBPHY1_CTRL_SET);
+	udelay(1000);
+
+	return !!(readl(USBPHY1_STATUS) & STATUS_DEVPLUGIN);
+}
+
 /* At default the 3v3 enables the MIC2026 for VBUS power */
 static void setup_usb(void)
 {
